In the epic "Star Wars" film franchise, Mark Hamill played Luke Skywalker, part of one of the most well-known father-son relationships ever portrayed on the movie screen. So it seems only fitting that the actor would acknowledge it on Father's Day. And he did: But like many fathers, Darth Vader couldn't resist going for the last word. A Twitter account purporting to be the Star Wars villain tweeted to Hamill: Even in a galaxy far, far away, you can't pick your relatives. Share this slide: